  "texts": [
    "We have demonstrated that the proposed MMS-LLaMA, integrating efficient token compression strategies into multimodal speech LLM frameworks can dramatically reduce computational costs while preserving high-level linguistic content.",
    "By incorporating an early AV-fusion module, a dynamically adaptive AV Q-Former, and a refined query allocation strategy with a speech rate predictor, we have achieved state-of-the-art AVSR performance, attaining a WER of 0.72% while using only 3.5 multimodal speech tokens per second.",
    "Moreover, our extensive experiments on the LRS3 dataset have confirmed that this method not only achieves Table 8: WER (%) of different methods at various SNR levels (dB).",
    "a superior WER but also reduces FLOPs by 35.7% compared to the previous LLM-based AVSR approach.",
    "While we have introduced an efficient multimodal speech LLM framework, its current focus is constrained to the AVSR task."
